FBIS4-45635 "jpten015___94037" JPRS-TEN-94-015 JPRS Environmental Issues 27 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA PAKISTAN Envoy Urges Transfer of Resources for Environment Programs Envoy Urges Transfer of Resources for Environment Programs BK2705062394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 GMT 27 May 94 BK2705062394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Urdu BFN [Text] At the United Nations, Pakistan has proposed that resources from the public sector, especially from industrially developed countries, should be transferred to developing nations for environmental protection so the process of sustainable development can be continued. Addressing the high-level meeting of the UN Commission on Sustainable Development, Begum Nusrat Bhutto, the prime minister's special envoy, proposed that resources should be allocated for creating awareness among the people about programs which can help protect the environment and eradicate poverty. She said that Pakistan believes in the process of sustainable development and like other countries is also deeply concerned over the deteriorating natural environment. She said that Pakistan feels concrete steps should be taken at global and national levels for continued development. Begum Nusrat Bhutto said that the Government of Pakistan is aware of the importance of environmental protection and the matter always remains in view while making decisions at every level.
